Class FrozenProperties

java.lang.Object
java.util.Dictionary<Object,Object>

java.util.Properties
org.postgresql.pljava.nopolicy.FrozenProperties
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable, Cloneable, Map<Object,Object>
public final class FrozenProperties extends Properties
An unmodifiable subclass of Properties.

The overidden methods violate the superclass API specs to the extent that the specs allow modification, or the returning of modifiable sets or collections.

When any overridden method would, per the spec, modify the map, the method will throw UnsupportedOperationException instead.

  • Constructor Details

    • FrozenProperties

      public FrozenProperties(Properties p)
      Constructs a FrozenProperties instance from an existing Properties instance.

      The instance will have a defaults list (also frozen) if p has defaults that have not been superseded by later settings. Defaults are flattened into a single default properties instance, even if p had a defaults instance chaining to another or a chain of others.

      Parameters:
      p - the instance whose entries are to be copied
